reviewText: Scott is awesome. Love this wacky journey through his past girlfriends. Very entertaining. Wish I had friends like his that stand by him.
Dumb movie. Baio is a brain dead star who can't act for beans.

I only made it 75% through. He wants you to feel bad for him because he has the standards of Brad Pitt or George Clooney, but is not famous anymore and is shallow so he can't get himself an Angelina or Amal. Very typical celebrity book except a little more whiny, less fun.
If you like Scott Baio than this is right up your Al's Diner
any girl in the 90s loves scott baio in charles and charge and this even though its reality tv is no different. he is a great guy . fun to look at and see how he is and acts outside of tv.
